  1 //! Background AI tasks — "ship to AI".
  2 //!
  3 //! A job is a prompt the assistant works on behind the scenes: it runs the full
  4 //! agent loop autonomously (in auto-accept mode, so changes actually land) while
  5 //! you keep working. Jobs are tracked with a status and persisted to
  6 //! `.ciabatta/ai/jobs.json`, so their results survive restarts and can be polled
  7 //! from the mind-map GUI or listed with `ciabatta ai jobs`.
  8 //!
  9 //! Each job runs on its own [`Assistant`] with an isolated conversation, so a
 10 //! background task never tangles with your interactive session's history.
 11 
 12 use std::path::PathBuf;
 13 use std::sync::Mutex;
 14 use std::sync::atomic::{AtomicU64, Ordering};
 15 
 16 use anyhow::{Context, Result};
 17 use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};
 18 use serde_json::{Value, json};
 19 use tokio::sync::mpsc;
 20 
 21 use super::{AiEvent, Assistant, Mode};
